{"id":"2007.09608","submitter":"Tuvi Etzion","authors":"Tuvi Etzion and Junling Zhou","title":"Large Sets with Multiplicity","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.CO","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Large sets of combinatorial designs has always been a fascinating topic in\ndesign theory. These designs form a partition of the whole space into\ncombinatorial designs with the same parameters. In particular, a large set of\nblock designs, whose blocks are of size $k$ taken from an $n$-set, is a\npartition of all the $k$-subsets of the $n$-set into disjoint copies of block\ndesigns, defined on the $n$-set, and with the same parameters. The current most\nintriguing question in this direction is whether large sets of Steiner\nquadruple systems exist and to provide explicit constructions for those\nparameters for which they exist. In view of its difficulty no one ever\npresented an explicit construction even for one nontrivial order. Hence, we\nseek for related generalizations. As generalizations, to the existence question\nof large sets, we consider two related questions. The first one to provide\nconstructions for sets on Steiner systems in which each block (quadruple or a\n$k$-subset) is contained in exactly $\\mu$ systems. The second question is to\nprovide constructions for large set of H-designs (mainly for quadruples, but\nalso for larger block size). We prove the existence of such systems for many\nparameters using orthogonal arrays, perpendicular arrays, ordered designs, sets\nof permutations, and one-factorizations of the complete graph.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 19 Jul 2020 07:16:36 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-07-21"}
